3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with an intelligent agent that interacts with the video frames to detect actions. 
4. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with an agent that interacts with the environment (video frames) to perform a task. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is also a possible category as the paper deals with action detection in videos, which is a multimedia application.
